---
import CustomImage from '@/components/CustomImage'
import ImageCarousel from '@/components/ImageCarousel'
import CardCarousel from '@/components/CardCarousel'
import StickyHeader from '@/components/StickyHeader'
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout'

const SITE_TITLE = 'SWRT 11'
---

<BaseLayout title={SITE_TITLE}>
	<div>
		<section
			class='relative w-screen h-screen left-1/2 right-1/2 -ml-[50vw] -mr-[50vw] overflow-hidden'
		>
			<video autoplay loop muted playsinline class='absolute inset-0 h-auto w-full object-cover'>
				<source src='/videos/swrt/couch-launch.mp4' type='video/mp4' />
				Your browser does not support the video tag.
			</video>
			<div class='absolute inset-0 bg-black/40'></div>
			<div
				class='relative z-10 flex h-full flex-col items-center justify-start pt-[10vh] px-5 text-center text-white'
			>
				<h1 class='title text-5xl sm:text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-bold'>{SITE_TITLE}</h1>
				<h2 class='text-md sm:text-sm lg:text-xl font-medium mt-4'>
					A SUBORBITAL CLASS PARTIALLY REUSABLE ROCKET
				</h2>
			</div>
		</section>

		<article class='prose prose-xl dark:prose-invert w-full max-w-none mt-8'>
			<h2 class='text-4xl font-bold'>Overview</h2>
			<p>
				The StormWorks Rocket Test 11, (SWRT 11), is the eleventh iteration of our suborbital class
				rocket, designed for testing and research in the upper atmosphere and near space. It
				features a powerful engine, advanced avionics, and a robust design to withstand the harsh
				conditions of high-altitude flight. SWRT 11 is partially reusable (The booster can be
				reflown), with a focus on rapid turnaround and cost-effective testing for a variety of
				payloads and experiments.
			</p>
			<CustomImage
				imagePath='/src/assets/images/stormworks/swrt/image-3.jpg'
				altText='SWRT 11 having a "launch" with an Atlas locomotive as the "payload".'
			/>
			<p>
				Almost anything can be launched by SWRT 11 so long as it fits within the mass limits. We've
				gone as far as launching entire locomotives on top of the stack, with less than ideal
				results. Honda Civics, Kei trucks, couches, and nuclear reactors have all been launched by
				SWRT with great success, and we're always excited to launch new and exciting payloads on our
				world class vehicle.
			</p>
			<CardCarousel>
				<div class='rounded-3xl bg-gray-300 dark:bg-gray-800 p-8 text-center'>
					<h2 class='text-2xl font-bold mb-4'>Key Specifications</h2>
					<CustomImage imagePath='/src/assets/images/stormworks/swrt/launch.jpg' altText='' />
					<table>
						<tr>
							<th class='text-left'>Height</th>
							<td>32 meters</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<th class='text-left'>Diameter</th>
							<td>3.75 meters</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<th class='text-left'>Mass</th>
							<td>6,000 mass (Dry)</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<th class='text-left'>Payload Capacity</th>
							<td>~15,000 mass to suborbit</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<th class='text-left'>Engine Type</th>
							<td>Liquid-fueled Khasenty air-breathing jet engine w/ electric assist.</td>
						</tr>
					</table>
				</div>
				<div class='rounded-3xl bg-gray-300 dark:bg-gray-800 p-8 text-center'>
					<h2 class='text-2xl font-bold mb-4'>First Stage</h2>
					<CustomImage
						imagePath='/src/assets/images/stormworks/swrt/land-wide.jpg'
						altText="SWRT 11's first stage, the booster, landing back on the ground after a successful launch."
					/>
					<p class='text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300'>
						SWRT 11's first stage is a powerful and immense booster designed for heavy lift and
						rapid reusability. It incorporates a single Khasenty 3 engine with electric assist
						giving a 0.2 second startup time, allowing SWRT to lift heavy payloads to suborbit with
						ease. The booster is designed for rapid turnaround with innovative landing legs and
						robust landing electronics, allowing it to return to the launch site for refurbishment
						and reuse in future missions.
					</p>
				</div>
				<div class='rounded-3xl bg-gray-300 dark:bg-gray-800 p-8 text-center'>
					<h2 class='text-2xl font-bold mb-4'>Second Stage</h2>
					<CustomImage
						imagePath='/src/assets/images/stormworks/swrt/stage-two.jpg'
						altText="SWRT 11's second stage immediately following stage separation."
					/>
					<p class='text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300'>
						The second stage of SWRT 11 is a compact and efficient upper stage designed for
						precision orbital insertion and payload deployment. It features a solid fuel engine
						optimized for performance, with a simple and reliable design to ensure mission success.
						The second stage is equipped with advanced avionics and guidance systems for accurate
						trajectory control, making it ideal for a wide range of suborbital missions and
						experiments.
					</p>
				</div>
				<div class='rounded-3xl bg-gray-300 dark:bg-gray-800 p-8 text-center'>
					<h2 class='text-2xl font-bold mb-4'>Payload Fairing</h2>
					<CustomImage
						imagePath='/src/assets/images/stormworks/swrt/fairings.jpg'
						altText="SWRT 11's payload fairing, shown here during flight."
					/>
					<p class='text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300'>
						SWRT 11's payload fairing is a sleek and aerodynamic enclosure designed to protect the
						payload during ascent and ensure a safe and successful deployment. It features a
						lightweight yet durable construction, with a streamlined shape to minimize drag and
						maximize performance. The fairing is equipped with advanced separation mechanisms for
						reliable payload release, making it suitable for a wide range of scientific instruments,
						technology demonstrations, and other suborbital experiments. After a mission, it
						parachutes back to the ground for recovery and reuse in future launches.
					</p>
					<table>
						<tr>
							<th class='text-left'>Diameter</th>
							<td>3.25 meters</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<th class='text-left'>Height</th>
							<td>5.75 meters</td>
						</tr>
					</table>
				</div>
				<div class='rounded-3xl bg-gray-300 dark:bg-gray-800 p-8 text-center'>
					<h2 class='text-2xl font-bold mb-4'>Video: Tower catch</h2>
					<video controls muted class='w-full aspect-video rounded-3xl'>
						<source src='/videos/swrt/tower-catch.mp4' type='video/mp4' />
						Your browser does not support the video tag.
					</video>
					<p>
						SWRT 11 has even been caught by a Starship style launch tower, just like SpaceX's own
						Superheavy boosters.
					</p>
				</div>
			</CardCarousel>
			<iframe
				class='w-full aspect-video rounded-3xl'
				src='https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zXbHP7V7J_o'
				title='SWRT 11 Launch Video'
				allowfullscreen></iframe>
			<p class='text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 text-sm mt-2 mb-10'>
				Video: SWRT 11 in action. <a
					class='text-blue-500 hover:underline'
					href='https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zXbHP7V7J_o'
					target='_blank'
					rel='noopener noreferrer'>Watch on YouTube</a>
			</p>
			<ImageCarousel
				images={[
					{
						path: '/src/assets/images/stormworks/swrt/hero.jpg',
						alt: 'SWRT 11 just after lift off, with the launch pad support structures pulling away and the rocket engulfed in flames and smoke.'
					},
					{
						path: '/src/assets/images/stormworks/swrt/tower.jpg',
						alt: 'SWRT 11 booster being caught by a Starship launch tower.'
					},
					{
						path: '/src/assets/images/stormworks/swrt/stage-sep.jpg',
						alt: 'SWRT 11 stage separation with the booster and upper stage drifting apart from an interior camera view.'
					},
					{
						path: '/src/assets/images/stormworks/swrt/stage-sep-ext.jpg',
						alt: 'External cinematic view of SWRT 11 during stage separation in flight.'
					},
					{
						path: '/src/assets/images/stormworks/swrt/first-land.jpg',
						alt: 'The first ever landing of an SWRT booster in 2021 by SWRT 8, marking a major milestone in the development of the SWRT program.'
					},
					{
						path: '/src/assets/images/stormworks/swrt/land-close.jpg',
						alt: 'Close-up of the SWRT 11 booster moments before touchdown.'
					},
					{
						path: '/src/assets/images/stormworks/swrt/land-train.jpg',
						alt: 'SWRT 11 booster landing on a rail car designed to catch the booster and bring it back to the launch site for refurbishment and reuse.'
					}
				]}
			/>
		</article>
	</div>
</BaseLayout>

<script>
	import { animate } from 'motion'
	const showAnimations = localStorage.getItem('animations') === 'true'

	if (showAnimations) {
		animate(
			'.title',
			{ y: [80, 0], opacity: [0, 1] },
			{
				duration: 2.5,
				opacity: { duration: 3 },

				offset: [0, 0.55, 0.75]
			}
		)
	}
</script>
